2
00:00:04,150 --> 00:00:07,140
Does a small country have an advantage over other small countries

3
00:00:07,140 --> 00:00:08,910
if it is a tax haven?

4
00:00:08,910 --> 00:00:09,900
Not necessarily.

5
00:00:09,900 --> 00:00:16,920
A small financial elite in that tax haven is going to be making money off

6
00:00:16,920 --> 00:00:23,880
of the huge sums that are taken in for the purpose of tax evasion, concealing

7
00:00:23,880 --> 00:00:30,030
the ownership of the money, concealing the owner of a corporation setting up

8
00:00:30,030 --> 00:00:31,910
shell companies, that sort of thing.

9
00:00:31,910 --> 00:00:36,460
So it's really a very small number of people on that island, or in that

10
00:00:36,460 --> 00:00:45,730
territory that are going to be making big money off of the huge deposits

11
00:00:45,730 --> 00:00:47,560
that are there.

12
00:00:47,560 --> 00:00:51,970
I think there's a conspicuous disadvantage in that some of these

13
00:00:51,970 --> 00:00:56,940
places are really quite non democratic, they're authoritarian,

14
00:00:56,940 --> 00:01:01,210
there are tremendous pressures for conformity, because what you've got

15
00:01:01,210 --> 00:01:02,560
going is an arrangement.

16
00:01:02,560 --> 00:01:08,250
It's a kind of a racket, a scam to one degree or another.

17
00:01:08,250 --> 00:01:13,360
There's an in crowd that is benefiting from this arrangement, and that is

18
00:01:13,360 --> 00:01:19,070
going to leave a lot of people who are butchers and bakers, and candlestick

19
00:01:19,070 --> 00:01:25,930
makers who are not sharing in the proceeds.

20
00:01:25,930 --> 00:01:29,290
Not like the top people are doing.

21
00:01:29,290 --> 00:01:34,590
So that the quality of the civil society of a tax haven can suffer,

22
00:01:34,590 --> 00:01:40,560
because it is a kind of a racket that is managed by relatively few people

23
00:01:40,560 --> 00:01:46,020
who are not interested in democratic values or procedures.

24
00:01:46,020 --> 00:01:50,520
Does specialization in a niche market make small countries vulnerable?

25
00:01:50,520 --> 00:01:51,980
Potentially, yes.

26
00:01:51,980 --> 00:01:59,140
If that market goes away and the small country is reliant on that particular

27
00:01:59,140 --> 00:02:05,140
industry or product, then it is going to have to scramble to find a way to

28
00:02:05,140 --> 00:02:12,000
replace the economic benefits that it has lost by specializing in a

29
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:13,510
particular niche market.

30
00:02:13,510 --> 00:02:20,060
Now, no modern small country is just going to be in one market, but there's

31
00:02:20,060 --> 00:02:23,420
going to be diversification.

32
00:02:23,420 --> 00:02:28,990
In small countries that do very well, such as the Scandinavian countries,

33
00:02:28,990 --> 00:02:35,350
you will find a variety of economic activities that are beneficial, so

