37
00:02:52,410 --> 00:02:56,580
Why might smaller countries have more realistic perspectives than larger

38
00:02:56,580 --> 00:02:59,620
countries about what is happening in the world?

39
00:02:59,620 --> 00:03:00,690
Interesting question.

40
00:03:00,690 --> 00:03:05,500
There are at least a few economists who have thought about this, and the

41
00:03:05,500 --> 00:03:14,890
conclusion that they have come to is that a developed, well run small

42
00:03:14,890 --> 00:03:22,080
country is going to develop a kind of a sensing system about conditions in

43
00:03:22,080 --> 00:03:28,540
the outside world, that there is a sense of vulnerability that motivates

44
00:03:28,540 --> 00:03:35,490
them to pay more careful attention to the forces in the outside world than

45
00:03:35,490 --> 00:03:39,920
is generally the case in larger societies that feel less vulnerable.

46
00:03:39,920 --> 00:03:44,270
That have more political power, that have more economic power, that have

47
00:03:44,270 --> 00:03:45,930
more military power.

48
00:03:45,930 --> 00:03:54,440
So in this sense, the model is that is the mouse in the mouse cat

